topic-001.title: React / React Server Components — Critical RCE Vulnerability (React2Shell / CVE-2025-55182)
topic-001.content: The vulnerability allows unauthenticated remote-code execution (RCE) via a bug in how React deserialises payloads for Server Components. Affected versions: React Server-Component packages 19.0, 19.1, 19.1.1, 19.2.0 (react-server-dom-webpack / parcel / turbopack). Patched versions released: 19.0.1, 19.1.2, 19.2.1. Risk: Even apps that don’t explicitly define Server Functions may be vulnerable if they support Server Components.

topic-004.title: Do not be shy to use AI tools!
topic-004.content: Sometimes it is better to accept the truth. If everyone is driving a car, walking by is a noble act, but it won’t get you where you need to go—not fast enough, not anymore. And that’s how it is with AI. I used to pretend I didn’t need it.
